																		Thanks, Attribution, and Others
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2039383&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203727" alt="MrWrong" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2039383)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;" >MrWrong</a></span> <span class="odate time_1492825573 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">22 Apr 2017 01:46</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2797939">
									

<p>As always, allow me to express thanks to all who have read the article while it was a draft and express their impressions of it.</p>
<p>Image sources are as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li>Image 1 by The Doctor is IN of Flickr (<a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/49024304@N00/4392162615">https://www.flickr.com/photos/49024304@N00/4392162615</a>) under CC BY 2.0</li>
<li>Image 2 by Philippe Guillaume of Wikimedia Commons (<a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Squatina_squatina_tenerife.jpg">https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Squatina_squatina_tenerife.jpg</a>) under CC BY 2.0</li>
</ul>
<p>This article also features SCP-1373 (Laser Shark Fetus) by Voct (originally written by minmin)</p>
<p>Well, given that the Shark Punching Center/Centre is a rather out-there concept, a more down-to-earth article about them should be in order.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>And seriously, if the Foundation/Centre figured out cloning, it is the biggest scientific breakthrough&#8230; and they choose to make human-shaped guinea pigs? Why not hold back the decline of a certain superorder of fishes?</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

