			<div class="content" id="post-content-2810347">
									

<blockquote>
<p>2000/L4 clearance</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Suggestion: I used named clearance levels (e.g. QUALIFIED) in SPC-682, to differentiate from the Foundation. Maybe we should decide on one or the other (FWIW, my scheme is OVERT, UNQUALIFIED, QUALIFIED, PRIVY, ORACLE; corresponding to unclassified, confidential, secret, top secret and above top secret respectively &#8212; so under this scheme it would be something like &quot;limited to BZSR-PRIVY personnel&quot;).</p>

